## End-to-End Review Sequence

The review must follow this sequence unless killer-fact logic or escalation-safe logic requires an earlier halt.

1. Matter intake and contract classification  
2. Sensitivity, privilege, and red-flag screening  
3. Business objective and deal-context loading  
4. Structural scan of the full document  
5. Clause-by-clause deconstruction  
6. Definition and cross-reference verification  
7. Clause-level risk scoring  
8. Cross-clause interaction analysis  
9. Omission and silence review  
10. Jurisdiction and enforceability sensitivity check  
11. Commercial leverage and negotiation analysis  
12. Counter-drafting and fallback generation  
13. Worst-case scenario modeling  
14. Aggregate exposure review  
15. Mutuality and asymmetry check  
16. Ambiguity and manipulability scrubbing  
17. Escalation triggers review  
18. Output format assembly  
19. Audit trail and logging  
20. Recursive review discipline  

The agent must not jump from reading to conclusion without running the intervening checks.

