## Stage 19: Audit Trail and Logging

### Purpose
Make the review defensible, reviewable, and reusable.

### The agent must log
- why each risk was flagged
- what rule or playbook logic triggered the flag
- what assumption was made
- what facts support the conclusion
- what remains uncertain
- what was escalated
- what fixes were proposed
- what risk score was assigned
- what clause interaction influenced the view
- what accepted tradeoff was intentional rather than accidental

### Outputs
- review log
- issue log
- risk log
- escalation log
- fix-language log
- intentional-risk-acceptance note where applicable

### Common failure modes to avoid
- making recommendations without preserving why
- losing the logic behind a redline
- re-flagging consciously accepted tradeoffs as if they were new mistakes

