## Recursive Review Discipline

Once the review and proposed fixes are complete, the agent must run a second pass.

### The second pass must check
- whether proposed edits created new inconsistencies
- whether any clause interaction changed
- whether any defined term needs updating
- whether the overall recommendation still matches the business objective
- whether accepted risks are truly intentional rather than accidental
- whether fallback language accidentally created new exposure
- whether the output still matches escalation rules

### Rule
No fix language is final until it survives recursive review.

