## Common Failure Modes This Playbook Prevents

This playbook exists to prevent:
- summarizing without analyzing
- spotting wording issues but missing business consequences
- reviewing each clause in isolation only
- ignoring missing terms
- overlooking cross-reference failures
- approving asymmetrical rights by accident
- giving red flags without solutions
- failing to aggregate exposure
- over-lawyering small issues while missing fatal ones
- failing to escalate
- treating familiar template language as safe
- ignoring Dish N Dash’s actual operating model
- accepting vague obligations that operations cannot execute
- missing how liability, termination, and payment stack together

